# 🎓 HireFlow — Viva Preparation Guide

## 1. What is HireFlow?

**HireFlow** is a **Recruitment Workflow System** — a full-stack web application that helps **recruiters** post jobs and manage applications, and helps **candidates** discover jobs, apply, and track their application status. It also includes an **AI-powered matching engine** that scores candidates against job requirements.

---

## 2. Tech Stack (MERN)

| Layer | Technology | Purpose |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| **M** — Database | **MongoDB** (via Mongoose ODM) | NoSQL document database, stores Users, Jobs, Applications |
| **E** — Backend | **Express.js** (v5) | Node.js web framework for REST API |
| **R** — Frontend | **React** (v18) with Vite | Single Page Application (SPA) UI |
| **N** — Runtime | **Node.js** | JavaScript runtime for the server |

### Key Libraries

| Library | Where | Why |
|---------|-------|-----|
| `bcryptjs` | Server | Hashes passwords before storing in DB |
| `jsonwebtoken` | Server | Creates JWT tokens for authentication |
| `helmet` | Server | Adds security HTTP headers |
| `cors` | Server | Enables Cross-Origin Resource Sharing |
| `express-rate-limit` | Server | Prevents brute-force / DDoS attacks |
| `morgan` | Server | HTTP request logging in development |
| `validator` | Server | Email validation |
| `mongoose` | Server | MongoDB object modeling (ODM) |
| `axios` | Client | HTTP client for API calls |
| `react-router-dom` | Client | Client-side routing (SPA navigation) |
| `lucide-react` | Client | Icon library |
| `vite` | Client | Fast build tool & dev server |

